def K_Means(df):                                                                    #function for K_Means Clustering 
    temp_df=df.iloc[:,1:4] 
    num_of_clusters=max(list(df['Class']))                                          #Assigning max_value_of class as number of clusters 
    print('Number of Clusters:',num_of_clusters)
    k_means=KMeans(n_clusters=num_of_clusters, random_state=1)
    df['cluster_class']=k_means.fit_predict(temp_df)
    External_Validate(df,'K means')                                                  #External validation of model 
    return df

def hiearchal_Classification(df):                                                   #function for hiearchal_Classification
    temp_df=df.iloc[:,1:4]
    num_of_clusters=max(list(df['Class']))                                          #Assigning max_value_of class as number of clusters
    clusters=AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=num_of_clusters, affinity='euclidean', linkage='ward')
    df['cluster_class']=clusters.fit_predict(temp_df)
    External_Validate(df,"Hierarchal Clustering")                                     #External validation of model
    return df

def External_Validate(df, method):
    acc = metrics.accuracy_score(df['Class'],df['cluster_class'])                                   #Validating on different valiadation methods
    f1 = metrics.f1_score(df['Class'],df['cluster_class'], average='weighted') 
    print("Accuray_Score for ",method,':', acc)
    print("F1_Score for ",method,':', f1)
    adj=adjusted_rand_score(df['Class'],df['cluster_class'])
    norm=normalized_mutual_info_score(df['Class'],df['cluster_class'])
    adjmut=adjusted_mutual_info_score(df['Class'],df['cluster_class'])
    fowlkes=fowlkes_mallows_score(df['Class'],df['cluster_class'])
    print("Adjusted Rand Score for ",method,':',adj)
    print("Normalized Mutual Info Score for ",method,':',norm)
    print("Adjusted Mutual Info Score for ",method,':',adjmut)
    print("Fowlkes Mallows Score for ",method,':',fowlkes)

def create_3d_scatter(df,method):    
    fig = plt.figure()
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')
    ax.set_title("Classification using "+ method)
    for i in df.cluster_class.unique():
        data=df.loc[df['cluster_class']==i]
        ax.scatter(data[df.columns[1]], data[df.columns[2]], data[df.columns[3]],label=i)
    ax.set_xlabel(df.columns[1]+' Label')
    ax.set_ylabel(df.columns[2]+' Label')
    ax.set_zlabel(df.columns[3]+' Label')
    ax.legend()

def create_2d_scatter(df,method):    
    fig = plt.figure()
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111)

The main objective of Task 1 is to show that the external validationn is not great on models like un-supervised which is K means here and is also the reason for low accuracy_score and f1_score.The reason is it can't map the clustered labels to the external labels given in the dataset i.e after clustering it gives its own labels to the predicted values but not according to the labels in the dataset. This can be overcome by mapping the labels correctly which needs to be done manually, but for very large a number of clusters it is not feasible.

Validation of DATASET 8 with the help of manual mapping of labels

# Function for K_Means Clustering
# df is given as an input parameter
def K_Means_2(df):
    coordinates=df.iloc[:, 1:18]
    SHS = {}
    for i in range(2,15):
        k_means=KMeans(n_clusters=i,init='k-means++',random_state=40)
        k_means.fit(coordinates)
        # Silhouette score(silhouette mean) for K_Means
        SHS[i]= metrics.silhouette_score(coordinates, k_means.labels_)
    Max_SHS = max(SHS, key = SHS.get)
    k_means=KMeans(n_clusters = Max_SHS,init='k-means++',random_state=40)
    #Generating clusters for datasets    
    df['cluster_class']=k_means.fit_predict(coordinates)
    Internal_Valiadtion(df, 'K means')
    return df

#function for Hierarchical_Classification
def Hierarchical_Clustering_2(df):  
    coordinates=df.iloc[:, 1:18]
    SHS = {}
    for i in range(2,15):
        Aglo_C=AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=i,affinity='euclidean',linkage='ward')
        Aglo_C.fit(coordinates)
        #Silhouette score(silhouette mean) for Hierarchical Clustering
        SHS[i]= metrics.silhouette_score(coordinates, Aglo_C.labels_)
    Max_SHS = max(SHS, key = SHS.get)
    Aglo_C=AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters = Max_SHS,affinity='euclidean',linkage='ward')
    #Generating clusters for datasets
    df['cluster_class'] = Aglo_C.fit_predict(coordinates)
    Internal_Valiadtion(df, 'Hierarchical Clustering')
    return df

 # Function for internal validation
 # df, method are given as input parameters    
def Internal_Valiadtion(df, method):
    print('CH Ratio for ',method,': '+ str(metrics.calinski_harabasz_score(df.iloc[:, 1:18], df['cluster_class'])))
    dist = metrics.pairwise_distances(df.iloc[:, 1:18])
    dunnindex = dunn(dist, df['cluster_class'])
    print('Dunn Index for ',method,': '+ str(dunnindex))

# function for creation of 2d scatter plot coloring them according to clustering
# df,method,column1,column2 are given as input parameters
def create_2dscatter_2(df, method, column1, column2):                                  
    fig = plt.figure()
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
    ax.set_title("Classification using "+method)
    for i in df.cluster_class.unique():
        #class allocated by the clustering algorithm 
        data=df.loc[df['cluster_class']==i]
        #passing two variables in scatter function                                            
        ax.scatter(data[df.columns[column1]], data[df.columns[column2]],label=i)       
    ax.set_xlabel(df.columns[column1]+' Label')
    ax.set_ylabel(df.columns[column2]+' Label')
    ax.legend()  
    ax.set_ylabel(df.columns[column2]+' Label')
    ax.legend()
